title: Tassel, late 16th–early 17th century
medium:
Medium: linen
Technique: braided and knotted
creditline: Bequest of Richard Cranch Greenleaf in memory of his mother, Adeline Emma Greenleaf
description: Pear-shaped linen tassel, braided and knotted.  Short loop attached to pear-shaped center unit, from which hang seven end chains fromed by small circular elements and connected to one another by loops.
